---
import LegalPage from "../../components/LegalPage.astro";
import { getLocalizedPath } from "../../i18n/site";

const locale = "en";
const updatedAt = "March 17, 2026";
const pageDescription =
  "This policy explains how the ISAF S.A. website uses or may use cookies and similar technologies.";
---

<LegalPage
  locale={locale}
  currentPage="cookie"
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description={pageDescription}
  updatedAt={updatedAt}
>
  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. What cookies are</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Cookies are small files stored on your device when you visit a website. They can help recognize the browser,
        remember certain preferences, and provide essential functionality or statistical information, depending on the
        purpose for which they are used.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. Current status of the ISAF website</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        As of the latest update of this policy, the ISAF S.A. website uses <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong>
        only after the user's express consent for analytics.
      </p>
      <p>
        Without consent, the Google Analytics 4 script is not loaded and analytics cookies are not activated.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the current implementation, no marketing pixels, advertising tracking tools, or other advertising
        profiling mechanisms are configured.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Strictly necessary cookies</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Certain storage technologies or technical identifiers may be necessary for the proper and secure operation
        of the website or hosting infrastructure. If such mechanisms are used, their purpose is to provide the
        service requested by the user and they are not used for advertising or profiling.
      </p>
      <p>
        In addition, the servers and technical services used to operate the website may normally generate technical logs
        or diagnostic information, such as IP address, access time, and browser information, for security and administration purposes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. Third-party cookies</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        After analytics is accepted, the website loads Google Analytics 4 provided by Google. This service may use cookies
        such as <strong>_ga</strong> and <strong>_ga_&lt;container-id&gt;</strong> or similar identifiers to distinguish users
        and measure website usage.
      </p>
      <p>
        In addition, certain external resources accessed by the user's browser, such as font delivery services, may involve
        technical data processing at connection level. These aspects depend on the respective providers and on how the browser
        interacts with external resources.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. How you can control cookies</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        You can control or delete cookies from your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>view stored cookies;</li>
        <li>delete all or certain cookies;</li>
        <li>block cookies for all sites or only for certain sites;</li>
        <li>set preferences regarding notifications before storing a cookie.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Disabling certain technical mechanisms may affect the proper functioning of some websites or online services.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">6. Legal basis</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Cookies strictly necessary for the website to function or equivalent technical mechanisms may be used based on
        technical necessity and legitimate interest relating to the security and operation of the service.
      </p>
      <p>
        Google Analytics 4 and the related analytics cookies are activated only on the basis of your consent. You can
        express your choice through the cookie banner displayed on the first visit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">7. Relation to the privacy policy</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Information regarding the processing of personal data in connection with the use of the website and contact form
        is available in the <a href={getLocalizedPath(locale, "privacy")} class="text-red-400 hover:text-red-300">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.08] bg-white/[0.03] p-6 sm:p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">8. Contact</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        For questions regarding the use of cookies on this website, you may contact us at
        <a href="mailto:office@isaf.ro" class="text-red-400 hover:text-red-300"> office@isaf.ro</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LegalPage>
